%N A282798 Decimal representation of the x-axis, from the left edge to the origin, of the n-th stage of growth of the two-dimensional cellular automaton defined by "Rule 505", based on the 5-celled von Neumann neighborhood.
%C A282798 Initialized with a single black (ON) cell at stage zero.
%D A282798 S. Wolfram, A New Kind of Science, Wolfram Media, 2002; p. 170.
%H A282798 Robert Price, <a href="/A282798/b282798.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..126</a>
%H A282798 Robert Price, <a href="/A282798/a282798.tmp.txt">Diagrams of first 20 stages</a>
%H A282798 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1503.01168">On the Number of ON Cells in Cellular Automata</a>, arXiv:1503.01168 [math.CO], 2015
%H A282798 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ElementaryCellularAutomaton.html">Elementary Cellular Automaton</a>
%H A282798 S. Wolfram, <a href="http://wolframscience.com/">A New Kind of Science</a>
